HTTP - HyperText Transfer Protocol

The most interested HTTP requests is XHR in browser console.

Format:
JSON -> { key : value }
XML -> <tag> some text </tag>

URI
path after main site name -> yandex.ru/path

Method
GET -> quick, unsecure, without body
POST -> slow, secure, with body

Status code
100 - Information
200 - Success
300 - Forwarding
400 - Clients errors
500 - Servers errors

Remote address
IP with port

Headers
path - the request way
contentType - application/json-xml
user-agent - current browser

SWAGGER - library for requests, for API documentation